comments: Date is for opening night performance of the show, "St. Louis Woman," at the Schubert Theatre in New Haven, Connecticut. "I Wonder What Became of Me" was performed by character Della Green played by Ruby Hill. "I Wonder What Became of Me" was not included in the show, "St. Louis Woman" when it opened on Broadway March 30, 1946. However, it was included in the pre Broadway performances in New Haven, Connecticut (opened February 14, 1946) and Boston, Massachusetts (opened February 19, 1946). Early in March 1946, when it played in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, the show was revised and this number was dropped.
